----
There is only one Garden
A Plot belongs to a Garden
There are many Plots

lets say our garden has one plot
the plot's dimensions are 60x60
so there are 4 boxes in the plot.
;;garden.txt
plot;60x60

- 2017-summer

we want to know what can we plant for:
- 2018-winter
- 2018-summer
- 2019-winter
- 2019-summer

INPUT: 
- garden.txt (map of the garden), 
- seasons

ruby tool.rb --garden garden.txt --next-season 2018-winter 
# --current-season 2017-summer 

OUTPUT:
- a text file for each season

2018-winter.txt
plot;60x60
BOX_1;BOX_2
BOX_3;BOX_4

plot = [box_1, box_2, box_3, box_4]
plot.draw
class Plot
  attr_accessor :boxes

  def draw
    @boxes.each {|box| box.draw}
  end
end

class Box
  def draw

  end
end

